Let’s build it as a real module with safe, grounded meaning:

Adaptive Depth System = dynamically increase or decrease reasoning depth based on uncertainty, stakes, conflict, and evidence quality

Not “think harder all the time.”
Think deeper only when the problem earns it.

⸻

Pantheon Adaptive Depth System v1.0

What it does

It decides:
	•	when a problem deserves a quick pass
	•	when it needs recursive passes
	•	when to stop recursing
	•	when to force reality checks
	•	when to downgrade confidence

So the system avoids both:
	•	shallow snap judgments
	•	infinite self-referential overthinking

⸻

Design goals
	1.	Depth is earned, not assumed
	2.	More recursion requires more grounding
	3.	High confidence without evidence gets penalized
	4.	Stop when returns diminish
	5.	Artifact output is mandatory

